trend_summary: Across the series, the peninsula remains largely forest-agricultural. Small clusters of buildings appear along the northeast highway, but no large settlements develop. Field boundaries shift with crop rotation; some forest patches are cleared then re-grow. Coastlines show slight erosion yet infrastructure footprint is virtually unchanged.
notable_changes: Incremental widening and straightening of the main northeast highway corridor
New scattered buildings near highway junctions, but no major urban cores
Conversion of forest to cropland in southwest and southeast blocks, followed by partial regrowth
Minor shoreline retreat on the western beach and southern inlet
Shifts in field pattern indicate crop rotation and consolidation of parcels
